  "texts": [
    "Moreover, in our opinion, the degree of realism exhibited by most of the above synthetic data sets is somewhat limited (see Fig. 7).",
    "The type of annotations represents another difference between real and synthetic data sets: in most real data sets, videos are globally annotated with a specific label (e.g., normal, abnormal), whereas in synthetic data sets, few of them present this type of annotation (i.e., ACD and GTA5Event).",
    "The other synthetic data sets contain frame annotations; therefore, it is possible to extract the exact time span in which the anomaly occurs.",
    "Finally, we point out that, among synthetic data sets, only LCrowdV is available online.",
    "Re-Id is the task for which the highest number of synthetic data sets has been generated, due to the considerable interest it has received by the scientific community in recent years and probably also to privacy restrictions that make the acquisition of real data sets particularly difficult for this task (Uner et They have been mostly generated using computer graphics engines (Synthetic18k, RandPerson, PersonX, VC-Clothes, GPR, GPR+, FineGPR, WePerson), mainly Unity and GTAV."
